content:
I ran rustc-perf locally using cachegrind, following the instructions here, but when I ran ./target/release/site, I got this message:

Defaulting to loading from `results.db`
Starting server with port=2346
Loading complete but no data identified; exiting.

How do I display the data? FWIW, there's a bunch of files in results/.
Some of the files in results (probably cgann-*) will be plain text and are the intended way to consume profile information from cachegrind

The site is only currently setup to work with perf stat results, which are collected with bench_local (whereas it sounds like you used profile_local: https://github.com/rust-lang/rustc-perf/tree/master/collector#profiling-local-builds)
Happy to see PRs updating documentation to make this clearer, and perhaps some changes to the collector to make it more obvious
I was hoping that rustc-perf would visualize the data for me since the output of cachegrind/callgrind when run on rustdoc is pretty overwhelming :sweat_smile:
this kind of data has to be visualised e.g. in KCacheGrind atm
